Feature: Bootstrap leaves no top-level "AGENTS.md" in the target directory

  Supersedes scenario 7d64bb8ed5a3f656 (features/templates/51-bootstrap-does-not-generate-bd-side-effect-agent-paths.gherkin, currently pinned in repos/shopsystem-templates/features/bootstrap_bd_init_side_effects.feature from lead-2gr / brief 002).

  Scenario 51 pinned a conjunction of two absence properties: no top-level "AGENTS.md" AND no file at ".claude/settings.json". Brief 003 (lead-0h1) commits bootstrap to writing a canonical ".claude/settings.json" per shop type — scenario 60 (c8002527857e0dd1, features/templates/60-bootstrap-writes-canonical-claude-settings-json-per-shop-type.gherkin) carries the positive pin. The ".claude/settings.json"-absence clause of scenario 51 is therefore retired; only the "no top-level AGENTS.md" clause survives, and this scenario carries that surviving clause forward as a standalone pin.

  The Implementer should retire scenario 51's content from repos/shopsystem-templates/features/bootstrap_bd_init_side_effects.feature when landing this scenario. The "bd init --skip-agents" mechanism (scenario 50 / 32d99f6d4a2dad37) remains the realization that produces the AGENTS.md-absence property; this scenario pins only the observable outcome.

  Scenario Outline: bootstrap leaves no top-level "AGENTS.md" in the target directory, regardless of shop type, because the shop's canonical agent surface is ".claude/agents/*.md" alone and bootstrap invokes "bd init" with "--skip-agents"
    Given an existing git repository at a target directory "<target>" containing no top-level "AGENTS.md"
    When I invoke the "shop-templates" bootstrap entry point with shop type "<shop_type>", shop name "<shop_name>", and target directory "<target>"
    Then the exit code is 0
    And the target directory contains no top-level file named "AGENTS.md"

    Examples:
      | shop_type | shop_name               | target                       |
      | bc        | shopsystem-messaging    | /tmp/example-bc-shop         |
      | lead      | shopsystem-product      | /tmp/example-lead-shop       |
